                    <div class="tab">
                        <div class="tab-wrap">
                            <label for="tab-0">9 Prices and payment</label>
                            <div class="tab-content">
                                <p>9.1 Before you place an order with a Supplier for delivery to your GlobalParcelForward Address, we suggest that you use the calculator on the Site to obtain an indicative price for us providing the Forwarding Service to you.</p>
                                <p>9.2 The full fee that you must pay to us for each order (the Fee) shall comprise:</p>
                                <p>9.2.1 the cost of the Goods ordered (which shall be zero where you have placed an order directly with a Supplier and have already paid the Supplier for those Goods); and</p>
                                <P>9.2.2 the Personal Shopper Fee or Distribution Service Fee (if applicable); and</P>
                                <P>9.2.3 the Forwarding Fee agreed with you.</P>
                                <P>9.3 The Personal Shopper Service Fee and Distribution Service Fee shall each be set out on the Site from time to time.</P>
                                <P>9.4 The Forwarding Fee will be agreed with you before we send the Goods to your Delivery Address.The Forwarding Fee will be dependent upon (i) the charges made by the Courier and (ii) the size and weight of the package as measured and determined by us when we receive the Goods from the Supplier at your GlobalParcelForward Address.</P>
                                <P>9.5 All prices on the Site are in pounds (£) sterling. Prices may change at any time. Where you place an order with us for the Distribution Service, we shall, provided that you comply with your obligations in condition 5, deliver the Goods to you (and charge the Distribution Service Fee to you) zero rated for UK VAT purposes.</P>
                                <p>9.6 Whenever we receive Goods at your GlobalParcelForward Address, we will contact you using the details you provided when you became a Registered Member (or subsequently) to confirm the full amount of the Fee and to take payment from you using your payment card (a Direct Payment). If we are unable to contact you in order to make a Direct Payment, or you are unable to make a Direct Payment for any reason, we will promptly send to you an invoice for the amount of the Fee (an Invoice Payment). For the avoidance of doubt, we will not dispatch the Goods to you until we have received full payment for the Goods and the entire Fee.</p>
                                <p>9.7 If we are unable to contact you within 10 business days of receiving Goods from a Supplier at your GlobalParcelForward Address, we may return the Goods to that Supplier.</p>
                                <p>9.8 You are responsible for the Courier’s costs where:</p>
                                <p>9.8.1 we return any Goods to you;</p>
                                <p>9.8.2 we return any Goods to the Supplier; or</p>
                                <p>9.8.3 any Goods are returned to us because you are not available or refuse to accept delivery of those Goods at the Delivery Address on the date of attempted delivery by the Courier.</p>
                                <p>9.9 Where, under condition 9.8 above, you are required to pay Courier costs, we will contact you so you may make a Direct Payment for those costs.</p>
                                <p>9.10 All payment card holders are subject to validation checks and authorisation by the card issuer. If the issuer of your payment card refuses to authorise payment we will not be able to send your Goods, will not be obliged to inform you of the reason for the refusal and we will not be liable for non-delivery. In these circumstances we will try to contact you again to obtain valid payment details. If you do not provide a successful Direct Payment promptly we will deal with the Goods as we see fit.</p>
                                <p>9.11 We are not responsible for your card issuer or bank charging you as a result of our processing of your Direct Payment.</p>
                                <p>9.12 All payment transactions will be processed on our behalf by our nominated payment merchant. This means that your credit/debit card details are provided directly to the payment merchant and are never revealed to us. The payment merchant shall operate a secure server to process your payment details. The payment merchant shall encrypt your credit/debit card information and shall authorise payment.</p>
                                <p>9.13 Refunds and cancellations: You cannot cancel a shipping order you have made once your shipment has been booked by us with the Courier; in such cases no refunds can be made. Refunds of shipping costs and compensation for Goods that are lost or damaged either in our care or during transit with a tracked Courier service will be treated in accordance with condition 10. No compensation or refunds of shipping costs will be made under any circumstances in respect of, regular mail, budget and untracked Courier services.</p>
